ies at $z\\sim0$ are $\\sim81$%-$84$% and $\\sim16$%-$19$%, respectively. The\nBNS merger rate per galaxy can be well determined by the host galaxy stellar\nmass, star formation rate, and metallicity, which provides a guidance in search\nfor most probable candidates of BNS host galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 10 Oct 2021 02:41:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-20"}
